"n.(感情等)突发 【英】 n. (感情等)突发(a sudden violent emotion or action) 【记】 par(变)＋oxy(尖锐) ＋sm→变尖锐→突发 【例】 paroxysms of anger/paroxysms of pain n. (感情疾病等的)突发 【记】pa怕, ro肉, oxysm－怕吃肉, 因为怕高血脂突发 【类】paroxysm: sudden = ruse: deceived突发是突然的 = 诡计是欺骗的 【记】par- 旁边 + oxygen 氧，旁边需要有氧气罐，因为突然发病，需要吸氧 paroxysm (n.)  ""sudden attack, convulsion,"" early 15c., from Middle French paroxysme (16c.), earlier paroxime (13c.), from Medieval Latin paroxysmus ""irritation, fit of a disease,"" from Greek paroxysmos ""irritation, exasperation,"" from paroxynein ""to irritate, goad, provoke,"" from para- ""beyond"" (see para- (1)) + oxynein ""sharpen, goad,"" from oxys ""sharp, pointed"" (see acrid). Non-medical sense first attested c.1600. Related: Paroxysmal."
